  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 21-year-old man comes to the physician because of painful, firm, dark bumps on his neck and jawline. He has no history of serious illness and takes no medications. His brother had a similar rash that improved with topical erythromycin therapy. A photograph of the rash is shown. Which of the following is the most likely underlying mechanism of this patient's condition?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Trichophyton infection of the superficial hair follicle"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Cutibacterium acnes colonization of the pilosebaceous unit"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Follicular obstruction with subsequent duct rupture"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Interfollicular penetration of the skin by distal end of hair"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Bacterial infection of the superficial or deep hair follicle"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=KM0Upg&anker=Zcbb25e2014ed0db4ae7a90c271cc8c21\" data-learningcard-id=\"KM0Upg\" data-anker=\"Zcbb25e2014ed0db4ae7a90c271cc8c21\" data-section-id=\"1-X2w00\" data-sememe-id=\"tSYXYK\">Trichophyton</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=KM0Upg&anker=Za4a3e3662bd0008d086b982768c4e5b9\" data-learningcard-id=\"KM0Upg\" data-anker=\"Za4a3e3662bd0008d086b982768c4e5b9\" data-section-id=\"1-X2w00\" data-sememe-id=\"SScy_b0\">dermatophyte</a>) infection of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xo0EVS&anker=Za466a64a9ff741e0365c57cc1db2aa1b\" data-learningcard-id=\"xo0EVS\" data-anker=\"Za466a64a9ff741e0365c57cc1db2aa1b\" data-section-id=\"h_ccLU0\">superficial</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Zf598c238bc50e50d52d2d3f67ffd39e1\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Zf598c238bc50e50d52d2d3f67ffd39e1\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">hair follicle</a> of the beard area causes <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hf0Kn2&anker=Z2e56fba90bdee58ba3fdff0113a67443\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hf0Kn2\" data-anker=\"Z2e56fba90bdee58ba3fdff0113a67443\" data-section-id=\"qSdC0p0\" data-sememe-id=\"fg1kuT0\">tinea barbae</a>, which can manifest with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"uCapF5\">pustules</a>. However, this condition more typically causes an inflamed region with an enlarging, raised, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"3wYSir\">erythematous</a> ring with a clear center and elevated edges. There is often associated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">hair</a> loss.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_58458dc407e03.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Localization: face of an older patient; right side above the mouth</p><p>Lesion: red, inflamed region with follicular papules above the mouth; additional papules on the chin</p><p>Additional symptoms: regional lymphadenitis, fever, reduced medical condition</p><p>Differential diagnosis: bacterial infection, HSV infection</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<i><a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=nk07oT&anker=Zee0acec6020327a325d68459ffcb8f7c\" data-learningcard-id=\"nk07oT\" data-anker=\"Zee0acec6020327a325d68459ffcb8f7c\" data-section-id=\"MYbMpH\" data-sememe-id=\"37bSlE\">Cutibacterium acnes</a></i> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=In0Yug&anker=Zd3b45ccb844489c4640c0435288e368e\" data-learningcard-id=\"In0Yug\" data-anker=\"Zd3b45ccb844489c4640c0435288e368e\" data-section-id=\"6Dcj2e0\" data-sememe-id=\"PZcWba0\">colonization</a> of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z32e40e783794457a0d4981677a14f7e4\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z32e40e783794457a0d4981677a14f7e4\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\" data-sememe-id=\"5KXiS_\">pilosebaceous unit</a> causes <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=nk07oT&anker=Z2f9ac019134dd9107bb69bdd35c62f24\" data-learningcard-id=\"nk07oT\" data-anker=\"Z2f9ac019134dd9107bb69bdd35c62f24\" data-sememe-id=\"YM0nMg\">acne vulgaris</a>, which manifests primarily on the face with inflammatory <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"sCatt5\">papules</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"uCapF5\">pustules</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Ze562e7aa25e368f0be0c7066c00f0243\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"YdXnoC\">nodules</a>, and <span data-sememe-id=\"ig1JET0\">comedones</span>. This patient does not have <span data-sememe-id=\"ig1JET0\">comedones</span>, and the distribution of lesions is atypical for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=nk07oT&anker=Z2f9ac019134dd9107bb69bdd35c62f24\" data-learningcard-id=\"nk07oT\" data-anker=\"Z2f9ac019134dd9107bb69bdd35c62f24\" data-sememe-id=\"YM0nMg\">acne vulgaris</a>.<img src='https://media-us.amboss.com/media/thumbs/big_5f2cee87cab7f.jpg' alt='Explanation Image' style='width: 100%; border-radius: 12px; margin-top: 16px;'><div style='margin-top: 16px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); padding-top: 16px;'><h5 style='font-weight: bold; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); margin-bottom: 8px;'>Image Description:</h5><div style='font-size: 0.9em; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.9); line-height: 1.6;'><p>Disseminated papules, pustules, and comedones on an erythematous base are visible on the seborrheic skin of the patient's forehead.</p><p>These findings are consistent with moderate acne vulgaris.</p></div></div></div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Follicular obstruction with subsequent duct rupture is characteristic of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=k80m53&anker=Zea51624c2ac7ddf22ff2a592e4ef5522\" data-learningcard-id=\"k80m53\" data-anker=\"Zea51624c2ac7ddf22ff2a592e4ef5522\" data-sememe-id=\"JUasVP\">hidradenitis suppurativa</a>. This condition most often affects the <span data-sememe-id=\"vT0As2\">intertriginous areas</span> (e.g., axillary, groin, perineal regions) and is associated with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=vH0AHh&anker=Z110d4126c6c4e2cb567242f4c0f4a60d\" data-learningcard-id=\"vH0AHh\" data-anker=\"Z110d4126c6c4e2cb567242f4c0f4a60d\" data-sememe-id=\"gzbFHw\">fistula</a> formation, scarring, and foul odor, which are not seen in this case.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=V80Gl3&anker=Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"V80Gl3\" data-anker=\"Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-section-id=\"HCWKtn0\" data-sememe-id=\"2UXTcx\">Pseudofolliculitis barbae</a> primarily affects <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>African American men</b></span> or <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>men with curly <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">hair</a></b></span> and is characterized by an <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>inflammatory reaction to ingrown <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">hairs</a></b></span> (e.g., after shaving). The <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">hair</a> either enters the interfollicular <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Zf73baeaff6ac94b7f4e9d771060c81d2\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Zf73baeaff6ac94b7f4e9d771060c81d2\" data-section-id=\"ftck1V0\" data-sememe-id=\"exaxv5\">epidermis</a> after exiting the follicular orifice (extrafollicular penetration) or penetrates the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Zd705c3204a95c4eb31deb2d7e832d3f6\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Zd705c3204a95c4eb31deb2d7e832d3f6\" data-section-id=\"ftck1V0\" data-sememe-id=\"Qxauw5\">dermis</a> before exiting the follicular orifice (transfollicular penetration). The resulting inflammatory reaction against the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">hair</a> leads to the characteristic finding of <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>painful <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"sCatt5\">papules</a></b></span> distributed along the <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>areas of facial <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">hair</a> growth</b></span>. Management of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=V80Gl3&anker=Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"V80Gl3\" data-anker=\"Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-section-id=\"HCWKtn0\" data-sememe-id=\"2UXTcx\">pseudofolliculitis barbae</a> includes cessation of shaving and adjunctive topical therapies (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z1f1addeb3de319446e00772a55dc3247\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z1f1addeb3de319446e00772a55dc3247\" data-section-id=\"avXQA-\" data-sememe-id=\"Zb1ZH20\">topical corticosteroids</a> to reduce inflammation and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antimicrobial therapy</a> to treat secondary infection).</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Bacterial <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qh0CUf&anker=Z32a834e1a3a0de9b8ff4240851cd5279\" data-learningcard-id=\"qh0CUf\" data-anker=\"Z32a834e1a3a0de9b8ff4240851cd5279\" data-section-id=\"PFcWRV0\" data-sememe-id=\"7pa4Il\">folliculitis</a> is characterized predominantly by <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"uCapF5\">pustules</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"3wYSir\">erythematous</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"sCatt5\">papules</a> on <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">hair</a>-growing areas of the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a>, not by the firm, dark <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Zdff645c223079108b72a307a8753ec7b\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"sCatt5\">papules</a> as seen in this case.</div>",
      "hint": "The image shows multiple small, dark, firm papules and some pustules on a man's shaved neck, which are manifestations of pseudofolliculitis barbae.",
