      "text": "Patient Information\nAge: 24 years\nGender: M, self-identified\nRace/Ethnicity: African American, self-identified\nSite of Care: office\nHistory\nReason for Visit/Chief Concern: “I have painful, itchy bumps on my face.” \nHistory of Present Illness:\n\n\n3-month history of lesions on cheeks, jaw, and neck\n\nlesions are firm, tender, and pruritic\n\n\nPast Medical History:\nasthma\nMedications:\n\nalbuterol\nfluticasone\n\nVaccinations:\nup-to-date\nAllergies:\n\npeanuts\nno known drug allergies\n\nPhysical Examination\n\n\nTemp\nPulse\nResp\nBP\nO2 Sat\nHt\nWt\nBMI\n\n\n37.1°C(98.8°F)\n64/min\n16/min\n125/75 mm Hg\n-\n190 cm(6 ft 2 in)\n70 kg(154 lb)\n19.4 kg/m2\n\n\n\n\nAppearance: comfortable, sitting in a chair\nSkin: a photograph is shown\n\n\nWhich of the following is the most appropriate initial step in management?",
      "choices": [
