      "correct_choice_id": 5,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=nk07oT&anker=Z1a87a10876340effbb23d6ccc721c671\" data-learningcard-id=\"nk07oT\" data-anker=\"Z1a87a10876340effbb23d6ccc721c671\" data-section-id=\"nvW70n0\">Topical retinoids</a> (e.g., <span data-sememe-id=\"5XViAG0\">tazarotene</span>) can be used as adjunctive therapy to reduce inflammation and thin the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=V80Gl3&anker=Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"V80Gl3\" data-anker=\"Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-section-id=\"HCWKtn0\" data-sememe-id=\"2UXTcx\">pseudofolliculitis barbae</a>, but they are not first-line treatments. Another initial step in management is more appropriate.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Topical <span data-sememe-id=\"i1bJgs\">mupirocin</span> is indicated for the treatment of mild <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qh0CUf&anker=Z668593101e7e880a19dbcdf0cdeb1a54\" data-learningcard-id=\"qh0CUf\" data-anker=\"Z668593101e7e880a19dbcdf0cdeb1a54\" data-section-id=\"PFcWRV0\">purulent skin and soft tissue infections</a> if <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=av0QA3&anker=Z8bc4e0b55c4b9457ef35d12f33cba663\" data-learningcard-id=\"av0QA3\" data-anker=\"Z8bc4e0b55c4b9457ef35d12f33cba663\" data-section-id=\"QKduTI0\" data-sememe-id=\"3oaSbl\">MRSA</a> coverage is desired, e.g., in patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qh0CUf&anker=Z32a834e1a3a0de9b8ff4240851cd5279\" data-learningcard-id=\"qh0CUf\" data-anker=\"Z32a834e1a3a0de9b8ff4240851cd5279\" data-section-id=\"PFcWRV0\" data-sememe-id=\"7pa4Il\">folliculitis</a>, which can manifest with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"uCapF5\">pustules</a>. Although <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=V80Gl3&anker=Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"V80Gl3\" data-anker=\"Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-section-id=\"HCWKtn0\" data-sememe-id=\"2UXTcx\">pseudofolliculitis barbae</a> can also manifest with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"uCapF5\">pustules</a>, it is a noninfectious inflammatory condition, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z6dc4c1f46474fba980154aff12c26a4a\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"uCapF5\">pustules</a> are typically sterile. Treatment with topical <span data-sememe-id=\"i1bJgs\">mupirocin</span> is not warranted.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Although <span data-sememe-id=\"UB1bZj0\">laser hair removal</span> can be used to treat <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=V80Gl3&anker=Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"V80Gl3\" data-anker=\"Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-section-id=\"HCWKtn0\" data-sememe-id=\"2UXTcx\">pseudofolliculitis barbae</a>, it is only indicated for persistent lesions and/or definitive treatment. Another initial step in management is more appropriate.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>Topical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z420f3c51bce93da9132e86041fe2fdc2\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z420f3c51bce93da9132e86041fe2fdc2\" data-section-id=\"ijcJZc0\" data-sememe-id=\"HOaKFk\">clindamycin</a> can be used as adjunctive treatment for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=V80Gl3&anker=Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"V80Gl3\" data-anker=\"Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-section-id=\"HCWKtn0\" data-sememe-id=\"2UXTcx\">pseudofolliculitis barbae</a> if there are signs of secondary infection or to decrease <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> flora that can cause inflammation, but it is not first-line treatment. Topical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z420f3c51bce93da9132e86041fe2fdc2\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z420f3c51bce93da9132e86041fe2fdc2\" data-section-id=\"ijcJZc0\" data-sememe-id=\"HOaKFk\">clindamycin</a> can also be used in the treatment of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=nk07oT&anker=Z173acbf09902a43dbcdf35e8a10b0007\" data-learningcard-id=\"nk07oT\" data-anker=\"Z173acbf09902a43dbcdf35e8a10b0007\" data-section-id=\"oYb0JH\">mild acne</a> vulgaris, but <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=nk07oT&anker=Z2f9ac019134dd9107bb69bdd35c62f24\" data-learningcard-id=\"nk07oT\" data-anker=\"Z2f9ac019134dd9107bb69bdd35c62f24\" data-sememe-id=\"YM0nMg\">acne</a> lesions are not limited to the beard region and affect all areas with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z0881e9e2b0c86d7a0a62be5a7d5212e4\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z0881e9e2b0c86d7a0a62be5a7d5212e4\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\" data-sememe-id=\"HdXKrC\">sebaceous glands</a> (e.g., face, shoulders, upper chest, and back).</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) CORRECT:</h4>\n<span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Cessation of shaving for a minimum of 8 weeks</b></span> is the first-line management of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=V80Gl3&anker=Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-learningcard-id=\"V80Gl3\" data-anker=\"Z1217b0b1b324fdf7fdeddb781c34e2f1\" data-section-id=\"HCWKtn0\" data-sememe-id=\"2UXTcx\">pseudofolliculitis barbae</a>, which typically arises after shaving, when short, recently trimmed <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">hair</a> curves and grows into or under the interfollicular <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> causing an inflammatory reaction. The condition is predominant in individuals with tightly curled <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z7d41ab7bd6b36ba8a82554b6790f2dde\" data-section-id=\"ptcLeV0\">hair</a> (e.g., Black men). Diagnosis is primarily based on clinical evaluation. Adjunctive therapies are aimed at reducing inflammation and thinning the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=nk07oT&anker=Z1a87a10876340effbb23d6ccc721c671\" data-learningcard-id=\"nk07oT\" data-anker=\"Z1a87a10876340effbb23d6ccc721c671\" data-section-id=\"nvW70n0\">topical retinoids</a>, low-dose <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z3733d22ef7bb87f743207060acda0451\" data-section-id=\"Pq1WA30\" data-sememe-id=\"8AbOlw\">corticosteroids</a>), and treating secondary infection (e.g., topical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotics</a>). Permanent <span data-sememe-id=\"UB1bZj0\">laser hair removal</span> can be considered in individuals with persistent symptoms or when cessation of shaving is not an option.</div>",
      "hint": "This patient presents with multiple firm, hyperpigmented papules and a few pustules in the beard region, which are tender and pruritic. These findings are consistent with pseudofolliculitis barbae.",
